des: "I needed an after-workout protein shake that was also a breakfast meal replacement that would keep me full until lunch. Everything I tried only lasted an hour or two before I got hungry again. Experimenting for something nutritious, delicious, and extremely filling, I finally created this. This smoothie is chock full of calories, carbs, fiber, protein, you name it."
ins: Blend soy milk, banana, yogurt, peanut butter, and tahini together in a blender. Add flax seed meal, almond flour, wheat germ, and protein powder; blend to combine.
